health_score.title: Health Score
health_score.description: Your Health Score brings rest and activity together into one number, showing how balanced your day is. It's the average of your Readiness and Activity scores.
health_score.baseline_info: A score of 80 represents your personal baseline. This is the point where your daily metrics align with your 30-day averages. Get above 80 and you're performing beyond your usual. Fall below 80 and you may want to focus on recovery.

readiness.title: Readiness
readiness.description: Readiness shows how prepared your body is for the day. It combines sleep quality, resting heart rate, and heart rate variability to give you an overall picture of your recovery.

activity.title: Activity
activity.description: Activity tracks your daily movement and exercise. It combines active points, steps, and move hours to show how active you've been throughout the day.

sleep.title: Sleep
sleep.description: Total time spent asleep based on your sleep tracking data. Quality sleep is essential for recovery and overall health.

resting_hr.title: Resting Heart Rate
resting_hr.description: Your heart rate measured during rest. Lower values typically indicate better cardiovascular fitness and recovery.

hrv.title: Heart Rate Variability
hrv.description: The variation in time between heartbeats. Higher HRV often indicates better recovery and stress resilience.

active_points.title: Active Points
active_points.description: Points earned through physical activity throughout the day. Higher intensity activities earn more points.

steps.title: Steps
steps.description: Total steps taken during the day. Aim for at least 10,000 steps for optimal health benefits.

move_hours.title: Move Hours
move_hours.description: Hours during which you recorded significant movement. Breaking up sedentary time is important for health.
